On Wed, 8 May 2002, Sharpe, Steven (Facilities Planning) wrote:

> I would like to install a modern brake switch that goes on at the very
> moment the brake pedal is depressed. Has anyone else done this? What parts
> were used and where was it mounted? Anybody got this up on a website?
>
> I've had too many close calls with the standard slow responding switch
> mounted on the master cylinder. I figure a modern switch would give those
> tailgaters another second of warning to start to react sooner.

If you want really quick reaction, install a switch the lights the brake
lights when the throttle is closed.  That way they'll see the lights
without having to wait for your foot to reach the brake pedal!

George

